The panel will include the following participants: 
- Isabel Cruz, CEO of the Mexican Association of Social Sector Credit Unions;
- Juan Carlos Urgiles, CEO of Jardín Azuayo, the largest savings coop from Ecuador;
- Elizabeth Campos, Vice-president (Vicegerente General) of Financiera FDL, the largest popular institution of Nicaragua;
- José Isidro Tzunún, General Advisor of Federural, main federation of savings coops of Guatemala 

This panel will be interesting for audiences interested in grassroots financial inclusion, social justice, popular finances, and regional development through technology.

Specific subjects will include:
1) Limits of financial inclusion in their region
2) Effect of digital payments in their communities
3) New opportunities for financial inclusion brought by open source digital payments technologies
